snippet.textDisplay:
Everyone talking about drinking bleach... I'm 100% sure the original source did not say to drink bleach. They probably told people you can disinfect water with bleach.
(CDC link at bottom.)
You can at about ⅛tsp of bleach per 2gal of water and let it sit for 30-60 minutes. It's also good to pour the disinfected water between two large containers a few times to let excess chlorine evaporate off, and disinfect both containers.
This will not hurt you or make you sick, it's much less than whatever is in an average pool. It's basically what's in your tap already.
You can also use potassium permanganate if you have it.
Often times bleach is easier for disinfecting water since most people don't boil water properly or sanitize the container they put the water into. Bleach is a better alternative and kills almost everything. You can mix 3parts bleach and 1 part water to make a disinfectant cleaner to clean surfaces and eating utensils before rinsing them well with your cleaned disinfected water.

Social media blows everything out of whack and people say "HE SAID DRINK BLEACH!" Yeah.. technically yes. He did. But a few drops compared to gallons. An amount you drink regularly anyway.
Here's the CDC telling you the same thing:
https://www.cdc.gov/healthywater/drinking/travel/emergency_disinfection.html
